Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces. Remove the ends from the @carrot{1}(halved lengthways, peeled and chopped into 1cm chunks) (no need to peel), halve lengthways and then chop into 1cm wide long strips. Chop into 1cm chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiling @water for the stock{650%ml} into a pan, stir in the @red wine stock paste{28%g}, pop on medium-high heat, bring to the boil and stir until dissolved. Reduce the heat to low and leave the stock to keep warm. Meanwhile, heat a large #wide-bottomed saucepan{} or a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). When hot, add the @British pork and oregano sausage meat{225%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Break it up with a #wooden spoon{} as it cooks.

Once browned, add the onion, carrot and @sliced mushrooms{150%g}, stir and cook until the veg has softened, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Add the garlic and cook, stirring for ~{1%minute}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Now, stir in the @Arborio rice{175%g} and cook until it's translucent at the edges, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir through the @tomato passata{1%tube}, bring to the boil and reduce to a simmer until the liquid has been absorbed, ~{2%minutes}.

Next, stir in a ladle of your stock. When the stock has been absorbed by the rice, stir in another ladle. Keep the pan on medium heat and continue stirring in stock, letting it absorb each time. This should take about ~{20-25%minutes}. Your risotto is done when your rice is 'al dente' - cooked through but with a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle. Once nearly cooked, add the @baby spinach{125%g} a handful at a time, stirring until wilted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

If the risotto isn't quite cooked but the stock has been absorbed, simply add a splash of water and keep cooking until the rice is tender. Once the risotto is cooked, remove from the heat. Add the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and a knob of @?butter{1%knob} (if you have some). Stir vigorously until everything is melted and combined.

Taste the risotto and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Serve in #bowls{} and enjoy!